    {
      "id": "c7467dc6_1323b766",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "message": "For reducing log there is another commit (Merged Yesterday): 138854: Fix huge logs produced when errors occur in k6 | https://gerrit.onap.org/r/c/cps/+/138854\n\nThis commit is all about high-cardinality issue that it fixed by introducing a REST url/endpoint tagging while performing GET/POST request as below :\n\nIn utils.js :\n\n- export function performGetRequest(url, metricTag)\n- export function performPostRequest(url, payload, metricTag)\n\nmetricTag - A string representing the metric tag to associate with the request.\nThis tag is used for monitoring and tracking the request and group by to avoid high-cardinality.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7957,
        "name": "Sourabh Sourabh",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "sourabh.sharma.lnf@gmail.com",
        "username": "sourabh_sourabh"
      },
      "updated": "2024-09-04 11:00:46.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "f9a966f6_e66191ff",
      "unresolved": false
    },
